results.name: Decimal expansion of ((11 + sqrt(85))/2)^(1/7).
comment: Heuberger and Wagner consider the number of maximum matchings a tree of n vertices may have.  They show that the largest number of maximum matchings (A333347) grows as O(1.3916...^n) where the power is the constant here.  This arises in their tree forms since each 7-vertex "C" part increases the number of matchings by a factor of matrix M=[8,3/5,3] (lemma 6.2).  The larger eigenvalue of M is their lambda = A333345 and so a factor of lambda for each 7 vertices.
link: Clemens Heuberger and Stephan Wagner, The Number of Maximum Matchings in a Tree, Discrete Mathematics, volume 311, issue 21, November 2011, pages 2512-2542; arXiv preprint, arXiv:1011.6554 [math.CO], 2010.
xref: Sequence growing as this power: A333347.
